        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:40PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 640 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles west of Grass Range, or 18 miles east of Lewistown, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grass Range and Forestgrove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
